<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="HR0003" sponsor="Norman K Thurston" designation="HR" otherSponsor="" otherHouse="Senate" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL0491" date="03-12-26" printDate="03-12 15:39" subVer="-2" minVer="2" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="hrules"><info><nextbuid>5</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="01/01/1800"><seclist><sect action="E" src="rule" buid="4" uid="HR2-5-S102_2026050620260506" sort="H02 05 01020020260506" mtype="section" effdate="05/06/2026">HR2-5-102</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="2" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="01/01/1800"/></seclist></aminfo><amendinfo level="1"/><aminfo anum="-1" effdate="01/01/1800"><seclist><sect action="E" src="rule" buid="4" uid="HR2-5-S102_2026050620260506" sort="H02 05 01020020260506" mtype="section" effdate="05/06/2026">HR2-5-102</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="2" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="01/01/1800"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">House Rules Resolution - Abandoning Legislation</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: Norman K Thurston</sponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><gdhead lineno="4">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5">This House rules resolution authorizes abandoning legislation.</gd><hphead lineno="6">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="7" slineno="0-7">This resolution:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="8" slineno="0-8" level="1">defines terms; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="9" slineno="0-9" level="1">establishes a process for a chief sponsor to abandon the chief sponsor's legislation.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="10" slineno="0-10" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="11">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12">Other Special Clauses:<ocl type="effdate" sort="2" numlevel="1" lineno="13" slineno="0-13">This resolution provides a special effective date.</ocl></oc><ra numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14">Legislative Rules Affected:<raent numlevel="1" lineno="15" slineno="0-15"><snhead>ENACTS:</snhead><sn num="HR2-5-102" src="rule" uid="HR2-5-S102_2026050620260506" buid="4" sort="H02 05 01020020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="16" slineno="0-16"><bold>HR2-5-102</bold></sn></raent></ra></lt><enacthead lineno="17"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="0-18">Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="4" num="HR2-5-102" type="enact" src="rule" uid="HR2-5-S102_2026050620260506" sort="H02 05 01020020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="19" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section numlevel="1" lineno="20" slineno="1-2" number="HR2-5-102" type="enact"><secline lineno="19">Section 1. <bold>HR2-5-102</bold> is enacted to read:</secline><catline lineno="20"><bold>HR2-5-102<parens/>. Abandoning legislation.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="4-13" dnum="_-o:1-e" numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="1-3" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1000" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(1)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="45" groupid="31" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">As used in this rule:</amend><subsection ssid="4-2" dnum="_-o:a-e" numlevel="1" lineno="22" slineno="1-4" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1001" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="7" groupid="6" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">"Chief sponsor" means the member of the House of Representatives who:</amend><subsection ssid="4-3" dnum="_-o:i-e" numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="1-5" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1002" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="10" groupid="8" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">approves a request for legislation for numbering; or</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="4-4" dnum="_-o:ii-e" numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="1-6" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1003" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="13" groupid="10" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">becomes the chief sponsor of legislation in accordance with <xref depth="3" refnumber="HR2-5-101">HR2-5-101</xref> or <xref depth="3" refnumber="JR4-2-101"><ln numlevel="1" lineno="25" slineno="1-7"/>JR4-2-101</xref>.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="4-5" dnum="_-o:b-e" numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="1-8" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1004" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="16" groupid="12" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">"Legislation" means a bill or resolution introduced for consideration by the <ln numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-9"/>Legislature.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="4-6" dnum="_-o:2-e" numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-10" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1005" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="19" groupid="14" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">A chief sponsor may abandon the chief sponsor's legislation by submitting to the chief <ln numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-11"/>clerk, before the legislation passes the Senate on third reading, an abandoning legislation <ln numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-12"/>form.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="4-8" dnum="_-o:3-e" numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="1-13" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1006" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(3)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="25" groupid="18" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">Once the chief clerk is in possession of the abandoned legislation, the chief clerk shall <ln numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="1-14"/>file the abandoned legislation.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="4-10" dnum="_-o:4-e" numlevel="1" lineno="33" slineno="1-15" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1007" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(4)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="31" groupid="22" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">No later than one legislative day after the day on which a chief sponsor submits an <ln numlevel="1" lineno="34" slineno="1-16"/>abandoning legislation form, the presiding officer shall publicly announce that the chief <ln numlevel="1" lineno="35" slineno="1-17"/>sponsor abandoned the legislation.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="4-11" dnum="_-o:5-e" numlevel="1" lineno="36" slineno="1-18" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1" space="false"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1008" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(5)</amend></display><subsection ssid="4-14" dnum="_-o:a-e" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2" placement="sameline"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1009" style="1" owner="e" level="1">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="57" groupid="41" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">Abandoning legislation has the effect of striking the enacting clause.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="4-15" dnum="_-o:b-e" numlevel="1" lineno="37" slineno="1-19" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1010" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="55" groupid="39" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">Legislation may not be revived once the chief sponsor submits an abandoning <ln numlevel="1" lineno="38" slineno="1-20"/>legislation form.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="4-12" dnum="_-o:6-e" numlevel="1" lineno="39" slineno="1-21" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1011" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(6)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="37" groupid="26" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">For legislation abandoned under this rule, the Office of Legislative Research and <ln numlevel="1" lineno="40" slineno="1-22"/>General Counsel shall note the abandonment on the legislation's webpage.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="4-16" dnum="_-o:7-e" numlevel="1" lineno="41" slineno="1-23" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1012" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(7)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="63" groupid="44" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">Nothing in this rule precludes a representative from introducing new legislation <ln numlevel="1" lineno="42" slineno="1-24"/>identical to the legislation abandoned under this rule.</amend></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="2" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="false" numlevel="1" lineno="43" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="43">Section 2.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="44"><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1" groupid="1" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="both">This resolution takes effect May 6, 2026.</amend></sectionText></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>3-12-26 3:19 PM</tm></rev></foot></leg>